 not available on the regular M2, with bold red brake calipers peeking through. The wheels will most likely be shod with grippy Michelin Pilot Sport Cup 2 tires, but there’s also word that the M2 CS could get sport, track, and ultra-track tire choices.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eBoth the bronze wheels and the brake calipers pop nicely against the model’s rather conservative flat grey exterior paint known as Brooklyn Grey, although other paint choices will include Sapphire Black and M Portimao Blue. All three paint colors are currently also available on the 2025 \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/bmw/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBMW\u003c/a\u003e M2. Inside, the M2 CS gets more aggressive sport bucket seats and subtle red CS logos on the door card and center console. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2026 BMW M2 CS\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1446\" height=\"837\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" sizes=\"(min-width: 750px) 750px, calc(100vw - 60px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDgz/screenshot-2025-05-27-114524.png 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDgz/screenshot-2025-05-27-114524.png 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDgz/screenshot-2025-05-27-114524.png 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDgz/screenshot-2025-05-27-114524.png 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDgz/screenshot-2025-05-27-114524.png 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDgz/screenshot-2025-05-27-114524.png 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDgz/screenshot-2025-05-27-114524.png 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.ima