 paddles only, meaning no manual transmission option. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"the-eighth-member-of-the-cs-clan\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe eighth member of the CS clan\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2026 BMW M2 CS\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1474\" height=\"796\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" sizes=\"(min-width: 750px) 750px, calc(100vw - 60px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAwMDg2/screenshot-2025-05-27-114535.png\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eThe CS badge stands for “Competition Sport,” a moniker for \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/bmw/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBMW\u003c/a\u003e’s specially formulated performance cars that exhibit technically innovative \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/bmw/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBMW\u003c/a\u003e components for enhanced power and handling. In total, there have been seven CS cars, starting with the 2017 \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/bmw/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBMW\u003c/a\u003e M4 F82 CS, but the true father of the CS cars was the 1988 E30 \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/bmw/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBMW\u003c/a\u003e M3 Evolution, a much-coveted collector’s car that’s tremendously valuable even today. The M2 CS will join this illustrious set, following in the footsteps of the 2020 \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/bmw/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBMW\u003c/a\u003e M2 CS F87 as well as the more recent M3 CS Touring and the M4 CS.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2026 BMW M2 CS\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2250\" height=\"1500\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" sizes=\"(min-width: 750px) 750px, calc(100vw - 60px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwOTAyNDIw/p90601581-the-new-bmw-m2-cs-2250px-902420.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eAll \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/bmw/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBMW\u003c/a\u003e CS cars get increased engine power, more aggressive suspension, lightweight construction, and enhanced aerodynamics, without compromising driver and passenger comfort. The automaker will supposedly create a CS version of the current M5, too. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"final-thoughts\"\u003eFinal thoughts\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/bmw/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBMW\u003c/a\u003e M CS cars are some of the best-performers the world has ever seen, and the M2 CS should prove to be a thrilling sports coupe to drive. If the rumors are true that it won’t get a proper manual transmission, our hearts will be broken (a little). The 2025 \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/bmw/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBMW\u003c/a\u003e M2 in bone stock form is one of the best driver’s cars available today, so to remove some of the engagement seems counterintuitive. That said, the additional power, lighter weight, better suspension, and more aggressive tire set should enhance the experience above the automatic version of the current base M2. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003csection\u003e\u003carticle\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca aria-label=\"View post: Ultra-Rare BMW 507 For Sale With Eye-Popping Pricetag\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/news/ultra-